Trash Radio: youtu.be/td__qXjVfMU PCA 169 Music Assignment For this assignment you should compose an image that captures an essence of music as you see it. You could approach this assignment from several angles, including musical instruments, people singing, concert scenes, etc. Many types of music have their own look and feel. Perhaps dark and moody, bright and jazzy. Show us how the music moves you. What It Took This was the first time that I shot at a festival so I shot a lot of pictures in manual mode, mostly at 800 ISO (shutter priority AE). I tried out a few shots mixed with more light on the public, but this silhouet looked better. I tried some smaller crops, but the more spotlights, the better it looked I cloned out a microphone on the stage that was left from a previous artist. I cloned out some lights of the sound and light crew in the front. My heart goes out to all people that died and got injured at the pukkelpop festival here in Belgium. www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-14590667

description._content: By sheer luck I noticed that the Ubuntu Quantal Quetzal wall paper submissions are open. This is my number on alternative for the contest which accepts only one submission this time. Excellent choice in my opinion. There are lots of great images in the group and no holiday photos this time. I ended up submitting this since this is a bit different than most landscape photos and this has been taken in Helsinki / Jakomäki which is the "most terrible looking suburb one can imagine." Of course above is said by those who probably have never visited there. This photo represents the other reality. My other alternatives www.flickr.com/photos/naggobot/7874171876/ www.flickr.com/photos/naggobot/7872502024/ I have to admit that I would have liked a bit more time to mull things over but unfortunately I had only few hours to decide. Feel free to disagree with my decision. Flickr stats will tell the truth in the end any how. ################## RAW processing in Photivo and subsequent cropping and 1.48 degree rotation adjustment in Gimp ##################

description._content: A simple picture capturing the sun as it rises over the Texas hills.

Timgharine on the path of Existence
-------------------------------------------------

Timgharine is the amazigh (native language in Morocco) word for women.

Photo taken during a survey in a village in the south of Morocco (El Maader, in the region of Tiznit, 90 km to the South of Agadir).

Those people are one of the most conservative people in Morocco and needless to say, you can’t dwell taking pictures of women (or people just like that). I was taking a break when I saw three women in their traditional outfit returning back to their village… I said to myself “I have to try a B&W picture”, in the mean time I was trying not to be noticed while taking the picture.

This picture so much reflects the life of these people whom have conserved their traditions in their struggle with life in a poor and resource-less environment.
